{
  "stem": "1282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Very few were illiterate in the what was accepted as the governmental language, the Ukrainian language, very few.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But all were literate, at least in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there were many, many peasant kids that didn't ever bother sending their kids to school at all.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was not uncommon to find complete families that were illiterate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was tradition, tradition that it was unheard of of a Jewish kid not to start going to Hebrew school at age of four.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was unheard of of a Jewish kid disobeying the governmental orders and not to go to school, to public school, no matter how hard it was.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a given that you go to school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You attend school.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And eventually, everyone was literate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was a way of life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Jewish people just did not disobey government orders.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, however, the bar mitzvahs were not as we know them today.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were very traditional.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it consisted of mostly the prayers to be done in the little shul that we had and possibly a small, little lunch.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not an elaborate bar mitzvah as today.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is all new.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is a new invention.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, you had to read from the Torah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had to be fluent in Ivrit, definitely.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had to do that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the concentration, knowing the Ivrit, knowing the Torah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That meant to be bar mitzvahed, that you have understood that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You have understood why you were bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The party was very small.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, in every respect, but we were not solely just Hasidic man here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was a-- wore a very modern outfit, suit and tie, and always a little hat, but not skull cap.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't wear this wide-brim hat.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
